Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Air Carnivore 'Black'
results.story: Debuting at CDG’s Spring/Summer 2021 runway show in Tokyo, the Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Nike Air Carnivore ‘Black’ brings back the cult-favorite 1993 cross trainer in a monochromatic finish. The retro silhouette’s defining features remain intact, including a high-cut neoprene collar and an adjustable Nike-branded midfoot strap, coated in reflective 3M for added visibility in low-light conditions. The rest of the upper is constructed from breathable mesh with tonal nubuck overlays at the toe and heel, the latter stamped with ‘Comme des Garçons Homme Plus’ in contrasting white lettering.

results.name: Mr. Doodle x Future Rider 'Puma Wordmark Embroidery'
results.story: The Mr. Doodle x PUMA Future Rider ‘Puma Wordmark Embroidery’ treats the lifestyle runner to a playful makeover. The color-blocked upper features a breathable white mesh base with a yellow felt Formstrip and synthetic leather overlays in orange and green. The British artist leaves his mark on the sneaker’s lateral side: ‘PUMA’ is embroidered in orange lettering on the left shoe, while ‘Mr. Doodle’ adorns the right. Unique doodle graphics decorate the lateral heel of each shoe.

results.name: ZX 1K Boost 'Bold Logo Graphic - Black Solar Yellow'
Aaron Kai x Stan Smith Primeblue Little Kid 'Doodles'
Wmns RS-Fast 'Tie Dye - Forever Blue Pink Lady'
Nike LeBron 18 Minneapolis Lakers (GS)
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Nike LeBron 18 GS ‘Lakers Heritage’ celebrates the storied NBA franchise’s beginnings in Minneapolis, Minnesota. In a nod to the Minneapolis Lakers’ early road uniforms, LBJ’s signature shoe showcases contrasting accents in powder blue and University Gold. The latter hue is prominently featured on the flexible collar and throughout the knit upper, which is mounted on a foam midsole with a visible Max Air unit nestled in the heel. ‘James 23’ branding adorns the custom sockliner.

results.name: Star Wars x ZX 2K Boost J 'Intergalactic Race'
Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS ‘Red Flint’ features traditional color blocking redolent of the shoe’s OG ‘Flint’ colorway from 1998. The mid-top makes use of the same blend of white leather and grey synthetic suede used on the original, contrasted by Gym Red detailing in lieu of the older shoe’s blue accents. The crimson hits of color land on the sneaker’s reflective mesh overlays, interior tongue and collar lining. A black Jumpman icon atop the tongue is complemented by a second Jumpman logo on the distinctive panther paw outsole.

results.name: Wmns ZX 1K Boost 'Bold Logo Graphic - Hazy Sky'
Darius Bazley x Two WXY 'My Home'
results.story: The Darius Bazley x New Balance Two WXY ‘My Home’ highlights vibrant primary colors on a performance hoops shoe inspired by the NBA forward. The royal blue textile upper is bolstered by wavy Kinetic Stitch detailing and a synthetic toe wrap accented with a subtle skyline graphic. Contrasting red accents land on the heel overlay and FuelCell foam midsole, supported by a midsole shank and a rubber outsole that wraps up the sidewalls for added traction.

results.name: adidas Superstar Bape ABC Camo Green
results.story: The BAPE x adidas Superstar 80s ‘ABC Camo’ makes over the sneaker icon with the Japanese streetwear brand’s signature flourishes. Chief among them is the green and brown camo print that floods the leather upper, reinforced with an instantly recognizable shell toe in off-white rubber. Mismatched adidas and BAPE branding is featured on the tongue and heel tab, as well as each shoe’s side panels, featuring adidas’ Three Stripes on one side and the BAPE Sta logo on the other. Metallic gold BAPE lace jewels are the finishing touch.

results.name: LeBron 18 EP 'Lakers Heritage'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 EP ‘Lakers Heritage’ features a color scheme that nods to the Minnesota roots of Los Angeles’ marquee NBA franchise. Reflecting the Minneapolis Laker’s road uniforms, LeBron James’ signature shoe makes use of a black Battleknit 2.0 upper flecked with gold fibers. A matching yellow collar is contrasted by a powder blue tongue and Concord-colored translucent heel counter. The lightweight build is placed atop a Cushlon midsole, enhanced with a full-length Zoom Air unit partially contained within a visible Max Air heel unit. This EP version sports an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts.

results.name: Wmns Cali Sport 'In Bloom - Desert Sage'
Vivienne Westwood x Gel Kayano 27 DE 'Lichen Green Brown'
results.story: Launching as part of a larger collection with the British fashion designer, the Vivienne Westwood x ASICS Gel Kayano 27 DE ‘Lichen Green Brown’ gives the lightweight running shoe a deconstructed look. Beige ripstop is utilized on the upper, fortified with no-sew overlays and partially covered in broken white netting for an unraveled aesthetic. Printed tiger stripes adorn the lateral side panel, along with Vivienne Westwood’s signature orb logo. Performance benefits include a molded TPU heel counter and a FlyteFoam Propel midsole with visible Gel cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Kyrie Low 4 EP 'Light Armory Blue'
results.story: The Kyrie Low 4 EP ‘Light Armory Blue’ features a semi-translucent textile upper with embroidered Swoosh branding and a synthetic leather heel tab. TPU fins are integrated into the laces to deliver a lockdown fit, while the low-cut padded collar offers a free range of motion. The sneaker rides on a full-length Cushlon foam midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot. A multicolor finish is applied to the computer-generated outsole, built with extra-durable rubber made for use on outdoor courts.

results.name: Nike Air Raid White Gum
results.story: The Nike Air Raid ‘White Gum’ delivers a summer-ready colorway of the 1992 hoops shoe specifically built for outdoor courts. An instantly recognizable cross-strap design secures an all-white upper constructed from mesh and leather. ‘Air Raid’ is embroidered on the lateral ankle strap, while ‘For Outdoor Use Only’ is embossed on the molded heel panel. The mid-top is mounted on a matching polyurethane midsole, reinforced underfoot by an extra-durable gum rubber outsole.

Aaron Kai x Stan Smith Primeblue Big Kid 'Doodles'
Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'British Khaki'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS ‘British Khaki’ delivers a refined take on the classic mid-top. Soft suede in a dark tan finish makes up the composition of the upper, equipped with a button stash pocket on the lateral collar and a zippered pouch on the medial side. A Jumpman icon in Bright Crimson stands out on the canvas tongue, matched by Nike Air and Cactus Jack logos on the heel of the left and right shoe. They’re joined by the Houston rapper’s personal branding hits on the medial-side midsole and semi-translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Tabi Instpump Fury Oxford Maison Margiela White
results.story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Tabi InstaPump Fury Oxford ‘White Porcelain’ delivers a blank-slate colorway of a hybrid silhouette that draws inspiration from both brands’ extensive archives. The familar inflatable cage of the Instapump Fury secures the all-leather upper, featuring a split-toe design lifted from the French fashion house’s Tabi boot from 1988. Lightweight cushioning is provided by Reebok’s shock-absorbing Hexalite technology, incorporated into an exaggerated midsole that recalls Margiela’s Retro Fit sneaker.

results.name: Crater Impact PS 'Light Bone Stone'
results.story: Developed for little kids, the Nike Crater Impact PS ‘Light Bone Stone’ features a lightweight build predicated on sustainability. The tan textile upper incorporates recycled fibers and reduced materials. The latter is achieved by using embroidered Swooshes and efficient overlays, including an orange webbing strap that folds in on itself to create lace loops. The sneaker rides on a powder blue Crater foam midsole with speckled sidewalls that indicate the inclusion of Nike Grind.

results.name: Billionaire Boys Club x InstaPump Fury Boost 'Water'
results.story: Designed in partnership with Pharrell’s long-running streetwear brand, the Billionaire Boys Club x Reebok InstaPump Fury Boost ‘Water’ showcases a cool aqueous hue throughout the laceless upper, crafted from Cordura fabric with a tonal inflatable cage. BBC’s spaceman logo adorns the rubber pump button atop the tongue, while Reebok’s Vector logo shines in metallic silver on the back heel. Responsive cushioning arrives via a decoupled Boost midsole, supported by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Tabi Instpump Fury Oxford Maison Margiela Citron
results.story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Tabi InstaPump Fury Oxford ‘Yellow’ showcases a mashup design that draws from iconic footwear styles linked to both brands. In lieu of traditional laces, the bright yellow inflatable cage of the 1994 Instapump Fury secures the upper of the black leather oxford. A split toe design recalls the French luxury house’s iconic Tabi boot from 1988. The slip-on’s exaggerated tooling, enhanced with Reebok’s Hexalite cushioning technology, takes inspiration from the Margiela Retro Fit sneaker, complete with a serrated tread under the heel.

results.name: Crater Impact PS 'Summit White Grey Fog'
results.story: Offered in little kid sizing, the Nike Crater Impact PS ‘Summit White Grey Fog’ highlights a neutral palette on a sustainable sneaker made with recycled materials and efficient construction techniques. The latter is exemplified by embroidered Swooshes and eyelet webbing that folds in on itself to create lace loops. The sneaker’s off-white textile upper is mounted on a lightly speckled Crater Foam midsole that incorporates Nike Grind, composed of discarded rubber scraps from footwear manufacturing.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki
results.story: Following on the heels of the coveted ‘Olive’ colorway from 2019, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘British Khaki’ reunites Jordan Brand with the Houston rapper. The upper is crafted with suede and canvas, accented with Bright Crimson details. The stash pouch makes a repeat appearance on the lateral collar, while new zippered detailing is added to the medial side. Mismatched Nike Air and Cactus Jack branding adorns the heel of the left and right shoe, with additional graphics on the midsole, outsole, tongue and lace lock.

results.name: Urbanstar x Air Force 1 '07 LX 'HELLO Pack - Black'
Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'British Khaki'
results.story: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘British Khaki’ scales the down the collaborative release for a new generation of sneaker enthusiasts. The mid-top is outfitted in a tan suede upper with stash pouches on both sides of the collar. Bright Crimson accents make their way to Jumpman branding on the canvas tongue, along with mismatched Nike and Cactus Jack logos on each heel. The sneaker rides on a soft foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.

results.name: Billionaire Boys Club x InstaPump Fury Boost 'Earth'
results.story: The Billionaire Boys Club x Reebok InstaPump Fury Boost ‘Earth’ showcases verdant earth tones on a retooled version of Steve Smith’s iconic design. Light brown Cordura fabric makes up the composition of the upper, which replaces traditional laces with a green-hued synthetic cage. The inflatable structure is activated by a crimson pump button decorated with BBC’s signature spaceman logo. adidas’ Boost cushioning is utilized on the decoupled midsole, reinforced underfoot by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Tabi Instpump Fury Oxford Maison Margiela Black
results.story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Tabi InstaPump Fury Oxford ‘Black’ applies a monochromatic finish to a hybrid design that blends luxury fashion with retro sport style. The leather low-top is secured with a patent leather inflatable cage borrowed from the 1994 Instapump Fury, while the split-toe design is taken from the French fashion house’s Tabi boot from 1988. Reebok’s Hexalite cushioning is integrated into the platform midsole, which recalls the bulky tooling of Margiela’s Retro Fit sneaker.

results.name: Crater Impact TD 'Light Bone Stone'
results.story: The Nike Crater Impact TD ‘Light Bone Stone’ adds highlighter accents to a versatile sneaker made with 20% recycled content by weight. Elastic no-tie laces allow for easy entry into a cream-colored textile upper that incorporates recycled polyester fibers. Looped eyelets are formed by bright orange webbing straps, which are mostly concealed under a midfoot overlay secured with contrasting stitching in Volt. The lightweight build rides on a powder blue Crater Foam midsole, partially composed of Nike Grind.

results.name: adidas ZX 8500 Overkill Graffiti
results.story: Developed in partnership with the Berlin-based retailer, the Overkill x adidas ZX 8500 ‘A-ZX Series’ represents the letter ‘O’ in the sprawling 26-part collection that explores the brand’s legendary ZX running franchise. The vintage running shoe features a maximalist design that takes the store name literally, highlighted by a clashing blend of vibrant hues throughout the mesh and suede upper. Graffiti-style branding includes ‘Overkill’ inscribed on the lateral toe and mismatched ‘OK’ and Trefoil tags on each tongue. The kicks come with a black mesh shroud that offers protection from errant paint drips.

results.name: LeBron 18 Low 'LeBronold Palmer'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 Low ‘LeBronold Palmer’ revisits a beverage-inspired theme previously featured on the LeBron 9 Low and LeBron 12 Low. Like its predecessors, this pair showcases a vibrant, tropical palette, highlighted by a yellow textile upper covered in a green palm-leaf print. A Bright Mango Swoosh is matched by a large-volume Max Air unit under the heel, which works in tandem with a React foam midsole to deliver a blend of lightweight cushioning and on-court responsiveness.

results.name: Star Wars x NMD_R1 Big Kid 'Rebels and the First Order'
Wmns Daybreak 'Paisley Swoosh - Pale Ivory Magma Orange'
Andersson Bell x Gel 1090 'Black Silver'
results.story: The Andersson Bell x ASICS Gel 1090 ‘Black Silver’ reworks the lifestyle runner with neutral tones and unique details inspired by mountain climbing boots. The Seoul-based fashion label confers a utilitarian aesthetic by supplementing the sneaker’s traditional lacing system with decorative bungee cords that feed through both webbing straps and metal speed hooks. The mesh and synthetic leather upper rides on a blacked-out EVA midsole, enhanced with Gel cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Crater Impact GS 'Summit White Grey Fog'
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Nike Crater Impact GS ‘Summit White Grey Fog’ delivers a versatile sneaker designed with sustainability in mind. At least 20% recycled content goes into the lightweight build, featuring an off-white textile upper that incorporates recycled fibers. A tonal midfoot overlay provides added stability, while a bright orange webbing pull tab assists with easy on off. Plush cushioning is provided by a Crater Foam midsole made in part with Nike Grind.

results.name: Andersson Bell x Gel 1090 'White Orange'
results.story: Designed in partnership with the Seoul-based fashion label, the Andersson Bell x ASICS Gel 1090 ‘White Orange’ treats the lifestyle runner to a rugged makeover inspired by mountaineering footwear. Three different sets of laces are integrated into the mesh and synthetic leather upper, including orange and black bungee cables fed through speed hooks and webbing straps. Warm earth tones up top are complemented by a dark yellow EVA midsole, featuring visible Gel cushioning under the heel for improved impact protection.

results.name: Crater Impact TD 'Summit White Grey Fog'
results.story: The Nike Crater Impact TD ‘Summit White Grey Fog’ delivers a sustainable-minded sneaker scaled down for little feet. Convenient no-tie elastic laces secure the off-white textile upper, made in part with recycled polyester fibers and equipped with a bright orange webbing pull tab at the heel. The lightweight build sits on a cushy Crater Foam midsole that incorporates about 15% Nike Grind, made up of rubber scraps left over from the footwear manufacturing process.

results.name: Crater Impact GS 'Light Bone Stone'
results.story: Constructed for big kids, the Nike Crater Impact GS ‘Light Bone Stone’ showcases vibrant accents on a versatile low-top made with at least 20% recycled content by weight. Recycled fibers are woven into the tan textile upper, accented with embroidered Swoosh branding and equipped with orange webbing straps that form the lace loops. Nike Grind is built into the Crater Foam midsole, as well as the reinforced rubber placed under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Andersson Bell x Gel 1090 'Glacier Grey Silver'
results.story: The Andersson Bell x ASICS Gel 1090 ‘Glacier Grey Silver’ delivers a mountaineering-inspired take on the lifestyle runner, courtesy of the Seoul-based fashion label. The layered mesh and synthetic leather supper is secured by traditional laces and two sets of bungee cords. One is integrated into webbing straps that surround the eyestay, the other is fed through metal speed hooks affixed to the sneaker’s side panels. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length EVA midsole with ASICS’ visible Gel technology in the heel.

results.name: Future Rider Retro 'White High Risk Red'
Wmns Chuck Taylor All Star Platform High 'Summer Denim - Vintage White'
results.story: The Converse women’s Chuck Taylor All Star Platform High ‘Summer Denim’ showcases a blank-slate palette on a fashion-forward edition of the classic silhouette. The upper replaces traditional canvas construction with washed denim in a Vintage White finish. Both the interior tongue and lining are covered in a multicolor floral print for a vibrant warm-weather touch. The high-top rests on a matching white platform midsole, featuring EVA cushioning for a comfortable ride.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 GS 'Black White'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 GS ‘Black White’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of the performance runner. The lightweight upper is crafted from ventilated black mesh with a wider toe box and low-cut collar. A set of interior webbing straps are integrated into the laces, offering midfoot lockdown and a personalized fit. The sneaker sits atop a plush foam midsole, featuring an Air Zoom unit under the ball of the foot for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Court Borough Mid 2 GS 'Black Game Royal'
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Court Borough Mid 2 GS ‘Black Game Royal’ features an essential two-tone color scheme on a basketball-inspired sneaker built for playtime. The upper combines easy-to-clean leather and breathable mesh on the collar, equipped with a webbing pull tab and secured with an adjustable hook-and-loop strap for a custom fit. The mid-top is supported by durable cupsole tooling, complete with flex grooves built into the rubber outsole for a natural stride.

results.name: Air Force 1 Low GS 'Patriots'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Air Force 1 Low GS ‘Patriots’ gets dressed in a familiar color combination that recalls New England’s NFL franchise. The retro low-top utilizes a white tumbled leather upper with a cut-out navy Swoosh and red mini-Swooshes embroidered on the vamp and lateral forefoot. Additional branding hits land on an elongated woven tongue tag and an added pull tab at the heel. The sneaker is nestled atop a durable rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide 'Black White'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide ‘Black White’ updates the performance running shoe with a lightweight build that places a premium on comfort and accessibility. Assembled on an accommodating last, the sneaker makes use of a breathable black mesh upper with zippered entry on the medial side. Additionally, no-tie elastic laces are designed to be secured using just one hand. The sneaker is mounted on a React foam midsole with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot.

results.name: Presto GS 'White Volt'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Presto GS ‘White Volt’ highlights a simplistic color scheme on a comfortable lifestyle runner originally billed as a T-shirt for feet. The lightweight build features a white mesh upper with a tonal midfoot cage and reinforced toe cap. Embroidered on the toe box is black Swoosh and ‘Just Do It’ in Volt lettering across the left and right shoe. Additional pops of Volt land on the heel and midsole, accented with five dots that nod to Nike’s short-lived Alpha Project initiative.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 PS 'Gen Zion'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Jordan Zion 1 PS ‘Gen Zion’ represents the debut colorway of Zion Williamson’s first signature shoe. Black mesh is utilized on the upper, bolstered with a white synthetic overlay that wraps around the heel and extends to the midfoot, culminating in a ‘Z’ formation on the lateral side. Additional nods to the athlete take the form of an all-over ‘Zion’ print on the collar and a ZW logo stamped on the left tongue, complementing a matching gold Jumpman on the right. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a plush foam midsole, reinforced by a decoupled icy rubber outsole.

results.name: Chuck Taylor All Star High GS 'Glow In The Dark Insect Print'
results.story: The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High GS ‘Glow in the Dark Insect Print’ is made for big kids with an abiding interest in entomology. The high-top utilizes a black canvas upper entirely plastered in a fluorescent green insect print that glows in the dark. Standard Chuck details remain intact, including chrome eyelets, winged tongue stitching and a circular All Star patch on the medial ankle. The sneaker sits atop a crisp white rubber midsole with contrasting black pinstripes and a Converse-branded license plate.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide 'Pure Platinum Chile Red'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide ‘Pure Platinum Chile Red’ delivers a combination of easy access and responsive cushioning. The light grey textile upper features convenient zippered entry on the medial side, along with a no-tie lacing system that can be easily secured with one hand. Integrated webbing straps offer a feeling of lockdown, while a foam tongue alleviates pressure at the top of the foot. The lightweight build is supported by a Nike React midsole, enhanced with springy Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot.
